The paper presents a method for domain adaptation in machine learning, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and other areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves training a classifier on multi-domain data, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation, which is a technique commonly used in computer security (cs.CR) and other areas of computer science.
